customrecordcustomfield.description:
Cross Match Field is the intersecting (join) field between this Control Saved Search and the selected Cross Match Control search. It needs to have the same data type of the Cross Match Control search.
For example, when the Cross Match Control search is an Employee search type, the Cross Match Field needs to be a searchable field of this Control Saved Search (e.g System Notes : Set By).
The Cross Match Field needs to be in a Script ID format (e.g. The Script ID format of System Notes : Set By is systemnotes.name).

<script>
function floHideNav()
{
//alert(window.location.href+"--"+top.location.href)
 //Hide the navigation if this window is not the top frame
 if(window.location.href!=top.location.href && top.location.href.indexOf("scriptlet")>0 && window.location.href.indexOf("&l=T")<0)
 {
     window.location.href=window.location.href+"&l=T";
 }
}
floHideNav();


//This script reloads the assistant after a new customization is spec'd
if(window.location.href.indexOf("?id=")>0 | window.location.href.indexOf("&id=")>0 && window.name=="newcust")
{
  //alert(window.opener.location.href)
  window.opener.location.reload();
  window.close();
}

</script>
